    <section class='html-notes'><h2 >Author Contributions</h2><div class='html-p'>Conceptualization, N.B. and S.I.,; methodology, N.B. and M.K.S.A.; validation, S.I. and N.B.; experiment, N.B. and S.I.; writing—original draft preparation, S.I., M.K.S.A. and S.P.; writing—review and editing, S.P.; funding acquisition, S.P. All authors have read and agreed to the published version of the manuscript.</div></section><section class='html-notes'><h2>Funding</h2><div class='html-p'>This work was supported by the European Union’s Horizon Europe Project, CUSTODES—A Certification approach for dynamic, agile, and reUSable assessmenT for composite systems of ICT proDucts and servicEs, and processes Grant Agreement No. 101120684 and CyberSecDome—An innovative Virtual Reality-based intrusion detection, incident investigation, and response approach for enhancing the resilience, security, privacy, and accountability of complex and heterogeneous digital systems and infrastructures, funded under grant agreement No. 101120779.</div></section><section class='html-notes'><h2 >Data Availability Statement</h2><div class='html-p'>The original data presented in the reserach are openly available in [<a href="#B10-sensors-24-04859" class="html-bibr">10</a>].</div></section><section class='html-notes'><h2 >Conflicts of Interest</h2><div class='html-p'>Author Shareeful Islam and Spyridon Papastergiou were employed by the company MAGGIOLI S.P.A. The remaining authors declare that the research was conducted in the absence of any commercial or financial relationships that could be construed as a potential conflict of interest.</div></section><section id='html-references_list'><h2>References</h2><ol class='html-xx'><li id='B1-sensors-24-04859' class='html-x' data-content='1.'>Application Programming Interface (API) Security Market Size, Share, Growth Analysis—Industry Forecast 2023–2030. Available online: <a href="https://www.skyquestt.com/report/application-programming-interface-security-market" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.skyquestt.com/report/application-programming-interface-security-market</a> (accessed on 8 February 2024).</li><li id='B2-sensors-24-04859' class='html-x' data-content='2.'>Khandelwal, D. The Impact of APIs on Modern Businesses|Nordic APIs|. Available online: <a href="https://nordicapis.com/impact-of-apis-on-businesses/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://nordicapis.com/impact-of-apis-on-businesses/</a> (accessed on 5 April 2024).</li><li id='B3-sensors-24-04859' class='html-x' data-content='3.'>Salt Labs. Latest State of API Security Report: 400% Increase in Attackers and More! Salt. Available online: <a href="https://salt.security/blog/latest-state-of-api-security-report-400-increase-in-attackers-and-more" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://salt.security/blog/latest-state-of-api-security-report-400-increase-in-attackers-and-more</a> (accessed on 16 April 2024).</li><li id='B4-sensors-24-04859' class='html-x' data-content='4.'>Li, C.; Lv, Q.; Li, N.; Wang, Y.; Sun, D.; Qiao, Y. A novel deep framework for dynamic malware detection based on API sequence intrinsic features. <span class='html-italic'>Comput. Secur.</span> <b>2022</b>, <span class='html-italic'>116</span>, 102686. [<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=A+novel+deep+framework+for+dynamic+malware+detection+based+on+API+sequence+intrinsic+features&author=Li,+C.&author=Lv,+Q.&author=Li,+N.&author=Wang,+Y.&author=Sun,+D.&author=Qiao,+Y.&publication_year=2022&journal=Comput.+Secur.&volume=116&pages=102686&doi=10.1016/j.cose.2022.102686" class='google-scholar' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Google Scholar</a>] [<a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cose.2022.102686" class='cross-ref' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>CrossRef</a>]</li><li id='B5-sensors-24-04859' class='html-x' data-content='5.'>Cannarile, A.; Carrera, F.; Galantucci, S.; Iannacone, A.; Pirlo, G. A Study on Malware Detection and Classification Using the Analysis of API Calls Sequences Through Shallow Learning and Recurrent Neural Networks. In Proceedings of the Italian Conference on Cybersecurity, Rome, Italy, 20–23 June 2022. [<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=A+Study+on+Malware+Detection+and+Classification+Using+the+Analysis+of+API+Calls+Sequences+Through+Shallow+Learning+and+Recurrent+Neural+Networks&conference=Proceedings+of+the+Italian+Conference+on+Cybersecurity&author=Cannarile,+A.&author=Carrera,+F.&author=Galantucci,+S.&author=Iannacone,+A.&author=Pirlo,+G.&publication_year=2022" class='google-scholar' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Google Scholar</a>]</li><li id='B6-sensors-24-04859' class='html-x' data-content='6.'>Almaleh, A.; Almushabb, R.; Ogran, R. Malware API calls detection using hybrid logistic regression and RNN model. <span class='html-italic'>Appl. Sci.</span> <b>2023</b>, <span class='html-italic'>13</span>, 5439. [<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Malware+API+calls+detection+using+hybrid+logistic+regression+and+RNN+model&author=Almaleh,+A.&author=Almushabb,+R.&author=Ogran,+R.&publication_year=2023&journal=Appl.+Sci.&volume=13&pages=5439&doi=10.3390/app13095439" class='google-scholar' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Google Scholar</a>] [<a href="https://doi.org/10.3390/app13095439" class='cross-ref' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>CrossRef</a>]</li><li id='B7-sensors-24-04859' class='html-x' data-content='7.'>EU Artificial Intelligence Act | Up-to-Date Developments and Analyses of the EU AI Act. Available online: <a href="https://artificialintelligenceact.eu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://artificialintelligenceact.eu/</a> (accessed on 2 June 2024).</li><li id='B8-sensors-24-04859' class='html-x' data-content='8.'>EU AI Act: First Regulation on Artificial Intelligence|Topics|European Parliament. Available online: <a href="https://www.europarl.europa.eu/topics/en/article/20230601STO93804/eu-ai-act-first-regulation-on-artificial-intelligence" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.europarl.europa.eu/topics/en/article/20230601STO93804/eu-ai-act-first-regulation-on-artificial-intelligence</a> (accessed on 6 August 2023).</li><li id='B9-sensors-24-04859' class='html-x' data-content='9.'>Basheer, N.; Pranggono, B.; Islam, S.; Papastergiou, S.; Mouratidis, H. Enhancing Malware Detection through Machine Learning using XAI with SHAP Framework. In Proceedings of the 20th International Conference on Artificial Intelligence Applications and Innovations(AIAI), Corfu, Greece, 27–30 June 2024. [<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Enhancing+Malware+Detection+through+Machine+Learning+using+XAI+with+SHAP+Framework&conference=Proceedings+of+the+20th+International+Conference+on+Artificial+Intelligence+Applications+and+Innovations(AIAI)&author=Basheer,+N.&author=Pranggono,+B.&author=Islam,+S.&author=Papastergiou,+S.&author=Mouratidis,+H.&publication_year=2024" class='google-scholar' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Google Scholar</a>]</li><li id='B10-sensors-24-04859' class='html-xx' data-content='10.'>API Call Based Malware Dataset. Kaggle. Available online: <a href="https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/focatak/malapi2019" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/focatak/malapi2019</a> (accessed on 8 May 2019).</li><li id='B11-sensors-24-04859' class='html-xx' data-content='11.'>Security and Privacy Controls for Information Systems and Organizations. 2020. Available online: <a href="https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/SpecialPublications/NIST.SP.800-53r5.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/SpecialPublications/NIST.SP.800-53r5.pdf</a> (accessed on 6 February 2024).</li><li id='B12-sensors-24-04859' class='html-xx' data-content='12.'>Alwaheidi, M.K.; Islam, S.; Papastergiou, S. A Conceptual Model for Data-Driven Threat Analysis for Enhancin